ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would highly recommend this class to another student. This is probably mostly because I love to code and this class allows you to learn about a topic and really get in there and learn by doing, which is my favorite kind of learning.
Yes, I would recommend this course! This course is very helpful, and also very interesting. Students can benefit a lot from this course.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This subject isn't applicable to my research.

I learn a lot of useful knowledge about decentralized systems, and I also practiced my programming skill through this course! My research is about large-scale parallel computing, and my research topic is related to decentralized systems. In a word, this course helps me a lot for my research.
I know more about how to develop realistic decentralized systems and also learn how to balance the tradeoff in different cases.
broaden my knowledge in decentralized system.
